# Auto-push after changes

When you finish a task that modifies files in this repository:

1. Check `git status` and commit all intentional changes (do not commit secrets).
2. Push to `origin` on the current branch without waiting for the user to ask.
3. Use Git at `C:\Users\Antara\AppData\Local\GitHubDesktop\app-3.5.8\resources\app\git\cmd\git.exe` if `git` is not on PATH.
4. Briefly report the commit hash and that the push succeeded.

Skip push only when the user explicitly says not to push, or when there are no changes to commit.
